text: Kiash Nanah (2 February 1936 - 29 January 2014) or Aïché Nana was a Lebanese- born Turkish actress, dancer and stripper. She was known for inspiring the dance of La Dolce Vita. She began her career when she was fourteen in 1950. Nana died on 29 January 2014, aged 77, at the Aurelia Hospital in Rome, Italy.
